<statement>
<p>116 is what percent of 80? <fillin characters="4" /><percent/> </p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>145</li></ul></p><p>Because we are asked for 116 of 80 we calculate,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\frac{{116}}{{80}}={1.45}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{1.45}\times{100}={145}</m>.</p>
<p>The result is greater than 100<percent/>, because the new amount is greater than the original amount.</p>
</solution>
</myopenmath>

